    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali123-kilavi">itu kāppumikutikkaṇ āṟṟāta talaivi talaivaṉpāṟ ceṉṟa neñciṉai nōkki aḻintu kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali123">
                <l>karuṅkōṭṭu naṟumpuṉṉai malarciṉai micaitoṟuñ </l>
                <l>curumpārkkuṅ kuraliṉō ṭiruntumpi yiyaipūta </l>
                <l>voruṅkuṭa ṉimmeṉa vimirtaliṟ pāṭalō </l>
                <l>ṭarumporuṇ marapiṉmāl yāḻkēḷāk kiṭantāṉpōṟ </l>
                <l>peruṅkaṭa ṟuyilkoḷḷum vaṇṭimir naṟuṅkāṉal;</l>
                <l rend="space">kāṇāmai yiruḷparappik kaiyaṟṟa kaṅkulāṉ </l>
                <l>māṇānōy ceytāṉkaṭ ceṉṟāymaṟ ṟavaṉainī </l>
                <l>kāṇavum peṟṟāyō kāṇāyō maṭaneñcē;</l>
                <l rend="space">kollēṟṟuc cuṟaviṉaṅ kaṭikoṇṭa maruṇmālai </l>
                <l>yallaṉōy ceytāṉkaṭ ceṉṟāymaṟ ṟavaṉainī</l>
                <l>pullavum peṟṟāyō pullāyō maṭaneñcē;</l>
                <l rend="space">neṟikoṇṭa  puḷḷiṉam vaticērum poḻutiṉāṟ </l>
                <l>ceṟivaḷai nekiḻttāṉkaṭ ceṉṟāymaṟ ṟavaṉainī </l>
                <l>yaṟiyavum peṟṟāyō vaṟiyāyō maṭaneñcē;</l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku,</l>
                <l>ellaiyu miravun tuyiṟuṟantu, pallū </l>
                <l>ḻarumpaṭa ravalanōy ceytāṉkaṭ peṟaṉacaii </l>
                <l>yiruṅkaḻi yōtampōṟ ṟaṭumāṟi </l>
                <l>varuntiṉai yaḷiyaveṉ maṭaṅkeḻu neñcē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l corresp="5">Into the fragrant seashore grove buzzing with bees where the great sea takes [its] sleep</l>
                <l corresp="4">like the one who lay listening to the big lute according to the custom of a meaning difficult [to understand]</l>
                <l corresp="3">along with the singing from the musical unisono humming</l>
                <l corresp="2">when the Tumpi bee gorges itself [on flowers] in harmony with the voice in which the Curumpu bee hums</l>
                <l corresp="1">on every flower if the fragrant Puṇṇai tree with black branches,</l>
                <l>you went for the one who caused [us] inglorious pain</l>
                <l>at night when we are prostrate with not seeing [him] as the darkness spreads.</l>
                <l corresp="6-8">Did you also get to see him. Please see, foolish heart</l>
                <l>You went for him who caused [us] unhappy pain</l>
                <l>in obscure evening when a school of murderous male sharks stand guard.</l>
                <l corresp="9-11">Did you also get to embrace him? Please embrace, foolish heart.</l>
                <l>You went for him who made our tight bangles loose</l>
                <l>at the time when the flock of birds who took the path joined [their] lairs.</l>
                <l corresp="12-14">Did you also get to know him? Please know, foolish heart.</l>
                <l corresp="15">That is to say,</l>
                <l>Abandoned by sleep day and night, many times</l>
                <l>longing to get to him who caused [us] unhappy pain [and] difficult affliction,</l>
                <l>deranged like the flood in the dark backwaters</l>
                <l corresp="16-19">my foolish heart suffers pitifully.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
